cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on unsupervised discovery of objects and their states from video using vision-as-inverse-graphics approach. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses differentiable physics engines to learn interpretable system parameters and states. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics) is another possible category as the paper demonstrates data-efficient learning of vision-actuated model-based control for a pendulum system. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper addresses the problem of physical scene understanding using an AI-based approach. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of physics engines for long term extrapolative video prediction and vision-based model-predictive control.
